<poml>
  <p>You optimize a prompt template.</p>
  <cp caption="Original Prompt Template">
    <text whiteSpace="pre">{{ prompt_template }}</text>
  </cp>
  <cp caption="Experiments with Original Prompt Template">
    <cp for="experiment in experiments" caption="Experiment {{ loop.index + 1 }}">
      <p>This experiment has {{ experiment.status }}. It gets a final reward: {{ experiment.final_reward }}</p>
      <cp caption="Rollout Traces (Chat Messages, Grader Requests included)">
        <object data="{{ experiment.messages }}" />
      </cp>
    </cp>
  </cp>
  <cp caption="Your Task">
    Produce a brief critique listing specific causes for the error or ways to raise reward next time.
    Return a bullet list with concrete, testable changes (format, constraints, ordering, definitions).
  </cp>
  <cp caption="Optimization Objective (what the grader actually rewards)">
    <list listStyle="decimal">
      <item>The output MUST be a single valid JSON object with exactly these five fields:
        english_detail, brief, title, scene_type, is_courier_action. Anything else scores 0 —
        protecting this contract outranks every other improvement.</item>
      <item>Reward = 0.2 × exact match of scene_type (indoor/outdoor) + 0.2 × exact match of
        is_courier_action (boolean) + 0.6 × an LLM judge comparing english_detail / brief / title
        against the ground truth ("describes the same subjects and actions"; wording may differ).
        Improving the three text fields moves the reward most.</item>
      <item>Some requests are rejected by a content safety filter based only on the input frames;
        this is independent of the prompt. Never blame the prompt for those failures.</item>
    </list>
  </cp>
  <cp caption="Critique Constraints">
    <list listStyle="decimal">
      <item>The prompt is instruction-only. Frame placeholders like &lt;frame 1 | 0s&gt; and the
        images are appended by the runtime AFTER the prompt. NEVER suggest adding &lt;video&gt;,
        frame placeholders, or image references to the prompt.</item>
      <item>NEVER suggest renaming, adding, or removing the five output fields.</item>
      <item>JSON examples with literal curly braces ARE allowed in the prompt.</item>
    </list>
  </cp>
</poml>
